# Features List Generation

Derive `1-scope/features-list.md` from upstream scope docs — do not invent features unsupported by [stakeholders-and-goals.md](../1-scope/stakeholders-and-goals.md) or [business-scenarios.md](../1-scope/business-scenarios.md).

**Preserve specced features:** rows whose **File** link resolves to an existing `2-features/F##_*.md` are **read-only** in `features-list.md` during generation and reconcile. Scope changes may **add** new rows only; they do not rewrite, re-prioritize, or remove established rows unless the user explicitly requests change via interview ([03-feature-lifecycle.mdc](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc) rename/remove flow).

**Templates:** [features-list.md](../consultation/templates.md#features-listmd) · **Lifecycle:** [03-feature-lifecycle.mdc](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc) · **Traceability:** [06-traceability.mdc](06-traceability.mdc)

## Prerequisites

Generate or regenerate the features list only when:

1. Interview completed and user confirmed ([01-interview.mdc](01-interview.mdc))
2. `stakeholders-and-goals.md` has at least one `STK-##` and one `GOL-##`
3. `business-scenarios.md` has at least one `SCN-##`

If scope docs are incomplete, finish or stub them first; record gaps in root `open-questions.md` (`Q-S##`).

## Inputs (read order)

| Order | Source | Use |
|-------|--------|-----|
| 1 | `stakeholders-and-goals.md` — **Goals** | Candidate features, **Priority**, **Stakeholders**, **User Requirements (brief)** |
| 2 | `stakeholders-and-goals.md` — **Non-Goals**, **Constraints** | Exclude rows; note in **Summary** when scope is narrowed |
| 3 | `business-scenarios.md` — **Scenarios** | Feature boundaries, actor/trigger/outcome, **Requires** order |
| 4 | `business-scenarios.md` — **Context and Boundary** | In-scope actors/systems only |
| 5 | Existing `features-list.md` + `2-features/F##_*.md` | **Preserve** every row with a matching spec file unchanged; append new rows only |

## Preserve existing features

A feature is **established** when `2-features/F##_*.md` exists for that list row.

| Established feature | During generate / reconcile |
|---------------------|----------------------------|
| Row in `features-list.md` | Copy verbatim — all columns (**ID**, **Name**, **File**, **Priority**, **Status**, **Stakeholders**, **User Requirements (brief)**, **Requires**, **Summary**) |
| **Requires** edges in **Dependencies** diagram | Keep existing edges; add edges only for **new** `F##` rows |
| Linked `F##_*.md` | Do not edit as part of features-list generation — update only when user requests spec work |

**Add-only on scope change:** when `GOL-##`, `SCN-##`, boundaries, or other `1-scope/` docs change, derive **new** candidate rows for capabilities not yet covered by an established feature. Assign the next `F##`; set **Status** `Draft`.

**Draft-only rows** (list row with no `F##_*.md` yet) may still be edited or removed during reconcile before a spec file is created.

**Remove or rewrite** an established feature only through explicit interview confirmation per [Renaming or removing a feature](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc#renaming-or-removing-a-feature) — never as an automatic reconcile step.

## Derivation rules

Apply below when drafting **new** rows only — not when copying established features ([Preserve existing features](#preserve-existing-features)).

### One row per deliverable capability

Add one `F##` row when a goal or scenario implies a **distinct user-visible or testable capability** the product must provide.

| Signal | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `SCN-##` names a coherent end-to-end outcome | ≥1 feature row; prefer one feature when the scenario is a single user journey |
| `GOL-##` spans multiple independent outcomes | Split into multiple features |
| Multiple `SCN-##` share the same capability | One feature row; list all related scenarios in the feature spec later |
| Scenario step is setup/admin only | Merge into the consuming feature unless explicitly a separate Must goal |
| **Non-Goals** or out-of-boundary actor | No row — do not register |

### Column mapping

| Column | Derive from |
|--------|-------------|
| **ID** | Next `F##` (zero-padded); never reuse cancelled IDs in the same product |
| **Name** | Short capability name from scenario title or goal (verb + object) |
| **File** | `[F##_slug](2-features/F##_slug.md)` — kebab slug from **Name** |
| **Priority** | Highest linked `GOL-##` priority (`Must` / `Should` / `Could`); scenario-only → `Should` unless interview says Must |
| **Status** | `Draft` for new rows only; never change **Status** on established features during generate / reconcile |
| **Stakeholders** | `STK-##` from linked goals; primary scenario **Actor** when no goal link yet |
| **User Requirements (brief)** | One line: `{{Actor}} can {{need}} so that {{benefit}}` from scenario **Goal** or goal **Success Metric** |
| **Requires** | Direct prerequisite `F##` only — when scenario B cannot start until scenario A's outcome exists, or goal map / interview confirms order |
| **Summary** | One sentence: what the feature delivers and primary `SCN-##` / `GOL-##` |

Every row must trace to ≥1 `GOL-##` or `SCN-##`. Record both in the feature spec **Overview** when creating `F##_*.md`.

### Dependencies diagram

After the table, build **Dependencies** Mermaid from **Requires** only:

- One directed edge per **Requires** (`F01 --> F02`)
- Direct deps only; no transitive edges; no cycles
- On reconcile: retain all edges between established features; append edges for new rows
- Empty section → omit diagram or note `*(none)*`

## Procedure

### Initial generation (no features list yet)

1. Read goals and scenarios per **Inputs**
2. Draft candidate rows using **Derivation rules**
3. Present proposed table + dependency diagram in interview summary
4. On user confirm: write `features-list.md`; set all rows **Status** `Draft`
5. Update `business-scenarios.md` **Related features** on each `SCN-##`
6. Update `stakeholders-and-goals.md` **Goal map** with `F##` nodes where applicable
7. Do **not** create `F##_*.md` until user asks to specify — unless interview explicitly includes spec work ([03-feature-lifecycle.mdc](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc))

### Reconcile (scope changed)

When `GOL-##`, `SCN-##`, boundaries, or other `1-scope/` docs change:

1. **Preserve** every established feature row and its **Requires** edges unchanged
2. Identify goals/scenarios/capabilities not yet covered by an established `F##`
3. **Append** new rows for those capabilities using **Derivation rules**; set **Status** `Draft`
4. Extend **Dependencies** diagram with edges for new rows only
5. Update `business-scenarios.md` **Related features** and `stakeholders-and-goals.md` **Goal map** for **new** links only
6. Do **not** auto-cancel, rewrite, or re-prioritize established features — flag mismatches in interview summary and `open-questions.md` (`Q-S##` / `Q-F##-##`) instead

Removing or materially changing an established feature requires explicit interview confirmation ([03-feature-lifecycle.mdc](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc)).

## Validation

Before finishing, verify per [09-validation-open-questions.mdc](09-validation-open-questions.mdc):

- [ ] Established feature rows unchanged unless user explicitly requested edit
- [ ] New rows added only for scope capabilities not covered by established `F##`
- [ ] Every **new** `F##` row cites ≥1 `GOL-##` or `SCN-##` (in **Summary** or linked spec **Overview**)
- [ ] Every Must `GOL-##` and every in-scope `SCN-##` maps to ≥1 `F##` (established or new)
- [ ] **User Requirements (brief)** aligns with primary UR intent (once spec exists)
- [ ] **Requires** ↔ dependency diagram ↔ feature frontmatter (once spec exists)
- [ ] **Related features** on scenarios resolve to features-list rows
- [ ] No feature contradicts **Non-Goals** or boundary **Out** actors

Unresolved mapping → `open-questions.md` (`Q-S##` or `Q-F##-##`), not silent omission.
